# Persistent Nginx Web Server (Namespace: persistent-server)

## 🧾 Resources Included

- `ConfigMap` with HTML
- `PersistentVolume` and `PersistentVolumeClaim`
- `Deployment` with an `initContainer`
- `NodePort` Service

## 🚀 Deployment Instructions

```bash
kubectl apply -f namespace.yaml
kubectl apply -f configmap.yaml
kubectl apply -f pv-pvc.yaml
kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml
kubectl apply -f service.yaml

🌐 Access Web Page
kubectl port-forward -n persistent-server svc/nginx-service 8080:80
Go to http://localhost:8080

🔁 To Test Persistence:
kubectl delete pod -n persistent-server -l app=nginx-persistent

kubectl delete pod nginx-persistent
kubectl apply -f nginx-persistent.yaml
kubectl port-forward pod/nginx-persistent 8080:80
curl http://localhost:8080
Check the site again — the HTML should persist!
